Before code, understand: a variable is just a box that stores a value.
Concept — English first
English to code translation:
"Store the number 5" → int num = 5;
"Store the word Sanjana" → String name = "Sanjana";
"Store true or false" → boolean pass = true;

Key insight: Every piece of data has a TYPE. A number is int. A word is String. True/false is boolean.
